Rwanda â€™s annual inflation rate
increased to 7.52 percent in August as energy and transport
costs increased, the  National Institute of Statistics  of Rwanda
said.  Inflation accelerated from 7.14 percent in July, the
Kigali-based agency said in a statement on its website today.
Prices climbed 0.4 percent in the month as the cost of energy
and water grew 0.7 percent and transport climbed 0.8 percent
